texts.text: >Thor throws everything into his attack with new resolve.
>The earth rumbles violently as Gozu-Tennoh falls apart.
...Thor, I expect no less from my most promising demon.
Follow your own path...
That is...enough...
>The light fades from Gozu-Tennoh's eyes, and all grows quiet.
It's over...isn't it?
...Follow my own path.
It seems your doubts have cleared.
You...!
The clone!
Didn't we beat you?
You might say I am Thor's shadow.
I cannot die in this world.
What do you mean?
This is a spirit world created by your doubts.
Even that Gozu-Tennoh,
he was only a trial you produced to dispel your uncertainty.
What?
A spirit world! Yes, it all makes sense now!
I KNEW this wasn't just an alternate world.
Have your doubts cleared, Thor?
Yes. The "correct way" matters not.
I have only to walk the path I believe in.
I think that's for the best.
Strength has no definite shape.
It's born from everything each of us holds dear,
and it reflects our hard-won convictions.
Hm, you have discerned what took me much wandering to understand.
It seems you are strong, yourself.
And [sys user_name], you are wasted on humankind.
Just like another lone warrior I respected.
Another...?
I wouldn't go that far.
Never mind. It is an old story.
Take a compliment.
I wish I could fight the three of you in an epic battle, but...
It appears we are out of time.
>The building sways, and the walls start to creak.
The anomaly in the Dragon Stream is disappearing fast!
Now that Thor is confident, this world is vanishing.
...I see.
I'm glad all is resolved, but it's too bad we can't do battle.
My journey has not ended.
If we meet again, let us spar.
Bulk up and give me a real challenge.
Of course!
I look forward to it.
Don't cry when you lose.
Make haste, humans. This place will not last much longer.
Right-o! It's finally my time to shine!
Yes, we're counting on you.
Let's return to our friends and our world.
>Kokoro's power grows as you move into the light...
(Kishin Thor... A noble warrior.)
(Maybe someday, somewhere...)
>You and the group disappear...
...Strange. My shadow is gone too.
Even so...
(Gozu-Tennoh.)
(The shadow said I created him, but those final words...)
(It was like Gozu-Tennoh himself imparted them to me.)
...No, impossible. This is my world.
(I will continue on my own.)
(I believe in my path of solitude.)
(I will walk it and persevere, achieving true strength in no time.)
(It will be my thanks...)
(to my mentor, the great leader of the Mantra Army.)
We're back, everyone!
[sys user_name]! Jeng Yun! You're safe!
Nice job! We were pretty worried there.
Thanks.
What about the demons?
No, thank you both.
Things calmed down here, thanks to your efforts over there.
They stopped showing up. We took care of the rest.
So, what happened over there?
It was a grand adventure.
No biggie.
...Can't you give us a better answer than that?
You had to know we'd ask.
Hey, hey. We can talk it over later.
Okay, y'all. Back to the hideout!
We'll wrap and call it a day.
>The line cuts, and each member returns to the hideout.
Jeng Yun?
...Ah, apologies. I was just thinking.
Would you lend an ear, [sys user_name]?
The root cause was the spirit world born from Thor's doubt,
but the demons that ran amok here,
don't you think they looked like the demons in the Mantra Army?
True.
Aren't you overthinking it?
Perhaps, but...
Here's what I think:
Gozu-Tennoh knew of Thor's doubts and dispelled them.
I can't say for certain since the truth is lost.
But we're free to feel that way.
>A crimson sunset washes over Jeng Yun and the others.
It's growing dark. The day is almost over.
I'm relieved the world is safe so I can enjoy this gentle scene.
And with friends, no less.
Unlike Thor, I don't think I can become stronger on my own.
When I lose my way, I trust my friends to steady my heart.
I agree.
I agree.
Still got a long ways to go.
The more the merrier, no?
I'll get much stronger yet.
Yes. Like you and Thor said, there's work to be done.
But I'll get much stronger yet.
We'll keep the world safe!
No greater power than conviction.
We'll walk this path together!
Yes, well said!
